
In This order issued Wednesday, FERC rejects the PX An=mendment No 22 and ISO 
Amendment No 36 in part and makes very strong statements about the need to 
have creditworthy parties for bilateral deals.  Only allows utilities to 
schedule their own resources to meet their own loads, or otherwise to have 
"support" from a creditworthy party.

